## Summary

Riso ERP uses Lesson Management without order modules. HQ/CM users need to manually create Lesson Allocations (LA) on UI — and update/delete them — so they can allocate students to lessons before contracts are signed. The system introduces a new "New Lesson Allocation" button in the Contact → Course tab, a multi-step modal form, CSV bulk import, and validation rules preventing date conflicts and past-date entries.

## Acceptance Criteria

### US 01 — As a HQ or CM, I want to create Lesson Allocation on UI or by CSV

| ID      | Feature                      | Acceptance Criteria                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         |
| ------- | ---------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| AC 01.1 | Create LA CTA                | Under Require Lesson Allocation table in Contact → Course tab, a "New Lesson Allocation" button is shown. Clicking it opens the New Lesson Allocation modal.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                |
| AC 01.2 | New Lesson Allocation form   | Form opens with: AY pre-filled by current AY; Location pre-filled by student's single active enrolled location (status = enrolled). If student has >1 active enrolled location → Location field is blank. If student has no active enrolled location → Location field is blank (shows all active enrolled locations or all locations user has affiliation with as suggestions). Course selection table appears after AY and Location are selected; shows all Course Masters with Course Offering (by AY) and Location Course (by Location); reloads when AY or Location changes; supports JP partial search by course name. |
| AC 01.3 | Config course and confirm    | User selects one or more courses → moves to next page to configure: Type (single select: Regular / Seasonal / Trial), Purchased Slot, Start date, End date (start < end). On confirm & save: redirected to Contact page; new LA(s) appear in the LA table in Course tab. LA is created with user-input data; Product details, student course id, package course, order remarks = No value (no order association); Course Offering and Location Course derived from selected course master & location.                                                                                                                       |
| AC 01.4 | LA creation validation       | 1. Same AY + Same Location + Same Course + overlapping start & end date → inline error at course section: _"The selected course has a duration that overlaps with another instance of the same course created earlier. Please adjust the start or end date."_ 2. Both start and end date are in the past → inline error under End date: _"End date must be a future date."_ 3. Start date > End date → inline error under both fields: _"Start date must be earlier than End date."_                                                                                                                                        |
| AC 01.5 | Bulk Create LA by CSV import | User can bulk create LAs via SF CSV import. Same data rules as AC 01.3; same validation as AC 01.4.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         |

### US 02 — As a HQ or CM, I want to edit or delete LA on UI

| ID      | Feature   | Acceptance Criteria                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        |
| ------- | --------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| AC 02.1 | Edit LA   | Editable fields: Start date, End date (only to a date **after** the original value — applies to both). New dates must pass validation in AC 01.4. If LA type = Trial: user can also edit Purchased Slot but only to a value **greater than** the original.                                                                                                                                                                                 |
| AC 02.2 | Delete LA | Delete is allowed **only** when LA's start date is in the future (> today). Confirmation dialog: _"All allocated lesson (if any) in this course will also be removed. This action cannot be reverted. Are you sure you want to delete this Lesson Allocation?"_ On confirm: LA is deleted and all allocated lessons are unlinked. On cancel: nothing changes. Delete button is **disabled** when LA's start date is in the past (≤ today). |

### US 03 — As a HQ or CM, I want to see summation of slot contracts

> ⚠️ US03 to be implemented together with PBT-1812. AC 03.2 is TBC.

| ID      | Feature                         | Acceptance Criteria                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    |
| ------- | ------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| AC 03.1 | Purchased Slot auto-calculation | LA.Purchased_Slot = sum of Contract.Slot for all contracts linked to the same LA, excluding Cancelled, Voided, and deleted (delete_flag = on) contracts. Recalculated when an existing contract is updated or a new contract is added for the same LA. |
| AC 03.2 | End Date auto-calculation (TBC) | LA.End_Date = latest end date among contracts linked to the same LA (excluding Cancelled/Voided/deleted). _(Status: TBC — pending confirmation)_                                                                                                       |

